<P>THE SENTENCE OF THE COURT-MARTIAL, Held at the HORSE-GUARDS, For the TRIAL of The Hon. Lieut. Gen. <HI>James Murray,</HI> Late GOVERNOR of <HI>MINORCA,</HI> ON THE TWENTY-NINE ARTICLES exhibited again&s;t him by Sir <HI>WILLIAM DRAPER.</HI></P>
<P>With His MAJESTY's Order thereon.</P>
<P>TO WHICH ARE ADDED, The WHOLE of the EVIDENCE on the Two ARTICLES of which the General was found Guilty;</P>
